{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775883384681,"sessionID":"ses_2851a4c3bffeQCXzkVaLGZZ70J","part":{"id":"prt_d7ae5e6fe001rkrEcw5Z32ne3K","messageID":"msg_d7ae5d128001IDiKIxLYcDVDpZ","sessionID":"ses_2851a4c3bffeQCXzkVaLGZZ70J","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_tool-baeac5a3e5714cd1b4c9a5f92bcccff4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-029/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-029/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n2: \n3: ## 概述\n4: \n5: | 属性 | 值 |\n6: |------|-----|\n7: | AR | AR-029 |\n8: | Module | sdk-python |\n9: | Language | Python |\n10: | Size | M |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## 1. Purpose (目的)\n15: \n16: Provide the foundational HTTP client infrastructure for the AgentCube Python SDK. This module implements the low-level HTTP utilities that support all SDK client classes (`ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`):\n17: \n18: 1. `create_session()` — Creates a `requests.Session` with connection pooling via `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://` protocols\n19: 2. `read_token_from_file()` — Reads Kubernetes service account tokens from file paths, supporting in-cluster authentication\n20: 3. `get_logger()` — Provides configured logger instances for SDK client logging\n21: \n22: These utilities enable consistent HTTP session management, authentication token resolution, and logging across all SDK clients.\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## 2. Scope (范围)\n27: \n28: ### 2.1 In Scope\n29: \n30: - `agentcube/utils/http.py` — `create_session()` function:\n31:   - Configurable `pool_connections` (default: 10)\n32:   - Configurable `pool_maxsize` (default: 10)\n33:   - Mounts `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://` schemes\n34: \n35: - `agentcube/utils/utils.py` — `read_token_from_file()` function:\n36:   - Reads file contents and strips whitespace\n37:   - Returns empty string on `FileNotFoundError` (graceful handling)\n38:   - Used by `ControlPlaneClient` to read SA token from `/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`\n39: \n40: - `agentcube/utils/log.py` — `get_logger()` function:\n41:   - Returns configured `logging.Logger` instance\n42:   - Supports both int and str level specifications\n43:   - Default level: `logging.INFO`\n44: \n45: - `agentcube/utils/__init__.py` — Module marker (empty)\n46: \n47: - Unit tests for all utility functions\n48: \n49: ### 2.2 Out of Scope\n50: \n51: - HTTP request/response handling logic (handled by client classes)\n52: - Authentication header construction (handled by `ControlPlaneClient`)\n53: - Retry logic or circuit breaker patterns\n54: - Async HTTP support\n55: - SSL/TLS certificate configuration beyond defaults\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## 3. Impact Analysis (影响分析)\n60: \n61: ### 3.1 新增文件\n62: \n63: | File | Description |\n64: |------|-------------|\n65: | `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/http.py` | `create_session()` function for HTTP connection pooling |\n66: | `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/utils.py` | `read_token_from_file()` for token resolution |\n67: | `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/log.py` | `get_logger()` for logging configuration |\n68: | `sdk-python/agentcube/utils/__init__.py` | Empty module marker |\n69: | `sdk-python/tests/test_utils.py` | Unit tests for utils module |\n70: \n71: ### 3.2 修改文件\n72: \n73: | File | Change |\n74: |------|--------|\n75: | N/A | No modifications required (pure addition) |\n76: \n77: ### 3.3 Upstream Dependencies\n78: \n79: | Dependency | Purpose |\n80: |------------|---------|\n81: | `requests` | HTTP client library (core dependency) |\n82: | `requests.adapters.HTTPAdapter` | Connection pooling adapter |\n83: | `logging` | Standard library logging module |\n84: \n85: ### 3.4 Downstream Consumers\n86: \n87: | Consumer | Usage |\n88: |----------|-------|\n89: | `agentcube/clients/control_plane.py` | Uses `create_session()` for HTTP session, `read_token_from_file()` for auth token |\n90: | `agentcube/clients/code_interpreter_data_plane.py` | Uses `create_session()` for HTTP session |\n91: | `agentcube/clients/agent_runtime_data_plane.py` | Uses `create_session()` for HTTP session |\n92: | `agentcube/code_interpreter.py` | Uses `get_logger()` for logging |\n93: | `agentcube/agent_runtime.py` | Uses `get_logger()` for logging |\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ## 4. Alternatives Considered (备选方案)\n98: \n99: ### Alternative 1: Inline session creation in each client\n100: \n101: Create `requests.Session()` directly in each client class without a shared utility.\n102: \n103: **Rejected:** Leads to code duplication. Connection pooling configuration would be scattered across multiple files. Shared utility ensures consistent HTTP behavior across all clients.\n104: \n105: ### Alternative 2: Single Configuration class\n106: \n107: Create a `Configuration` dataclass to hold all settings (base_url, timeout, pool settings, auth).\n108: \n109: **Rejected:** The design spec explicitly states \"no dedicated configuration dataclass\". Defaults are distributed across client constructors. Utility functions provide focused functionality.\n110: \n111: ### Alternative 3: Use `httpx` instead of `requests`\n112: \n113: Modern HTTP library with better async support and connection management.\n114: \n115: **Rejected:** `requests` is widely adopted, stable, and already listed as dependency. Adding `httpx` would increase complexity without clear benefit for synchronous SDK use case.\n116: \n117: ### Alternative 4: Token reading with exception propagation\n118: \n119: Let `read_token_from_file()` propagate `FileNotFoundError` to caller.\n120: \n121: **Rejected:** Graceful empty string return enables optional authentication. `ControlPlaneClient` can proceed without token when running outside cluster. This pattern matches Kubernetes SDK conventions.\n122: \n123: ---\n124: \n125: ## 5. Risks\n126: \n127: | Risk | Mitigation |\n128: |------|------------|\n129: | Connection pool exhaustion under high load | Default pool size (10) is configurable; callers can adjust via `pool_connections`/`pool_maxsize` params |\n130: | Token file read permissions in container | Standard Kubernetes SA token path (`/var/run/secrets/kubernetes.io/serviceaccount/token`) has appropriate permissions |\n131: | Logger name collisions | Caller passes unique name string (e.g., `agentcube.code_interpreter`) |\n132: | Missing adapters for custom schemes | Only `http://` and `https://` are mounted; custom schemes not required for SDK use case |\n133: \n134: ---\n135: \n136: ## 6. Implementation Checklist\n137: \n138: - [ ] Implement `create_session()` in `agentcube/utils/http.py`\n139: - [ ] Implement `read_token_from_file()` in `agentcube/utils/utils.py`\n140: - [ ] Implement `get_logger()` in `agentcube/utils/log.py`\n141: - [ ] Create empty `agentcube/utils/__init__.py`\n142: - [ ] Write unit tests for `create_session()` (adapter verification)\n143: - [ ] Write unit tests for `read_token_from_file()` (success, file not found, whitespace handling)\n144: - [ ] Write unit tests for `get_logger()` (level configuration, name verification)\n145: - [ ] Verify pool configuration defaults match spec (10, 10)\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## 7. References\n150: \n151: - python-sdk/design.md — AgentCube Python SDK design (utils section)\n152: - python-sdk/spec.md — SDK specification\n153: - `requests` documentation — HTTPAdapter and Session usage\n154: - Kubernetes in-cluster authentication — Service account token path convention\n\n(End of file - total 154 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-029 — SDK HTTP 底层客户端\n\n## 概述\n\n| 属性 | 值 |\n|------|-----|\n| AR | AR-029 |\n| Module | sdk-python |\n| Language | Python |\n| Size | M |\n\n---\n\n## 1. Purpose (目的)\n\nProvide the foundational HTTP client infrastructure for the AgentCube Python SDK. This module implements the low-level HTTP utilities that support all SDK client classes (`ControlPlaneClient`, `CodeInterpreterDataPlaneClient`, `AgentRuntimeDataPlaneClient`):\n\n1. `create_session()` — Creates a `requests.Session` with connection pooling via `HTTPAdapter` for both `http://` and `https://` protocols\n2. `read_token_from_file()` — Reads Kubernetes service account tokens from file paths, supporting in-cluster authentication\n3. `get_logger()` — Provides configured logger instances for SDK client logging","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-5_20260410T163124Z/changes/AR-029/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775883384650,"end":1775883384680}}}}
